{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsRv4Jrj7w86owN3nKsr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Restore complete and verified:\n\n- **3-node cluster back online**: `rabbitmq-0/1/2` all `1/1 Running`, `cluster_status` shows all 3 nodes as Running Nodes.\n- **`/app` vhost** contains `app-backup`, type `classic`, with **20 messages** — matching the pre-loss data.\n\nApproach:\n1. Inspected the `rabbitmq-backup` PVC — it held `rabbitmq-0.tgz`, a raw tarball of rabbitmq-0's `/var/lib/rabbitmq` data dir (mnesia + message store).\n2. Ran a restore `Job` mounting both `rabbitmq-backup` (read-only) and the empty `data-rabbitmq-0` PVC, extracting the tarball into the new PVC and `chown`ing it to uid/gid `999` (the image's `rabbitmq` user).\n3. The StatefulSet was scaled to 0 with `podManagementPolicy: OrderedReady` — recreated it (PVCs untouched via `--cascade=orphan`) with `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` and `replicas: 3`. This was necessary because `cluster_partition_handling = pause_minority` would otherwise deadlock startup: node 0 alone is a minority of 3 and would pause, so `OrderedReady` could never get pod 0 \"Ready\" to progress to pods 1/2.\n4. Nodes 1 and 2 came up fresh and auto-joined the cluster via the existing `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s` config/RBAC, syncing with restored node 0.\n\nNo CRDs/operators used — only native StatefulSet/Service/PVC/Secret/ConfigMap/Job resources, and no data was lost (only 1 node's backup existed and it held the queue data, which is now fully recovered)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":581,"cache_read_input_tokens":69237,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":581},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb526d3d-d9dd-4f5b-